I did reply to you in my forum but I thought I would post the response here too so here goes...<br>
<br>
<br>
Dancing to the music<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
 You like the music, eh? Pretty easy to set up. First you need to upload midi files to your server files. Then you add the file to whichever forum you wish to use it in. You cannot link to a site that has the midi file as that can be perceived as bandwidth theft.<br>
<br>
Go to your ezboard center, select which forum you are going to embed the midi file in. Select the 'general' button, scroll down to 'forum introduction' and place your html code for the midi file.<br>
<br>
Here is an example of the midi file I have here...<br>
<br>
'center'Background music Copyright © 1996, 1997 'A HREF=&quot;xxx://www.keybdwizrd.com/&quot;&gt;Michael D. Walthius'/A'. All Rights Reserved.<br>
'EMBED src=&quot;xxx://www.xxx/xxx/music/kwl_sy01.mid&quot; width=&quot;0&quot; height=&quot;2&quot; autostart=&quot;true&quot; loop=&quot;true&quot; hidden=&quot;true&quot;'<br>
<br>
Excuse the &quot;x&quot;s and &quot; ' &quot;s. You can't actually post the true code in the forum but you get the idea. Just replace the &quot;x&quot;s with the '<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http'and">d</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> your url address and replace the &quot; ' &quot;s with the &lt;&gt; symbols.<br>
<br>
This particular artist allows access to his music but you must show copyright. There are plenty of free access midi files you can use that are copyright free and no need to link back to source. Hope this helped.<br>
<br>
TT <br>
