Basically it's like you coming into my home and using my stereo to play whatever music you want at full volume without caring whether I like it or not.<br>
<br>
Effectively that's exactly what background music that starts automatically is doing, whether of not you can stop it is irrelevant to me.  I tend to have a low opinion of those that use it.<br>
<br>
If you want music on your site then make the user click the play button to start it.  That way you don't annoy a whole heap of people (when music was first being used on the net it was cool but then everyone started doing it).  Usually when I hear background music I reach straight for the volume control and turn it all the way down.<br>
<br>
The other problem with background music is that on some computers it stops all other sounds from coming through including new message notifications like the ones in Yahoo Messanger, ICQ and simliar programs which can be very disruptive to conversations on the net. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/ubestonnet.showPublicProfile?language=EN>bestonnet</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 131<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(2/8/02 5:01 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Suggestions box!</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> As this is the busiest thread in the entire forum perhaps it should be made a separate board. I noticed that other communities do this.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
